                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/8425: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-25T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1927—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>101. Your No. 246, March 24, 3 p.m. There is no basis whatsoever for the
                    statement you report as carried by United Press. No change has been made in the
                    orders issued Admiral Williams and repeated to you in Department’s No. 72 of
                    February 25, 2 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
